4540098.headline: Starbucks Reports Q2 Fiscal 2022 Results
4540098.description: May 3 (Reuters) - STARBUCKS: :STARBUCKS - QTRLY CONSOLIDATED NET REVENUES UP 15% TO Q2 RECORD $7.6 BILLION.STARBUCKS - Q2 GAAP EPS $0.58; NON-GAAP EPS OF $0.59.STARBUCKS - Q2 INTERNATIONAL COMPARABLE STORE SALES DECREASED 8%; Q2 CHINA COMPARABLE STORE SALES DECREASED 23%.STARBUCKS - Q2 COMPARABLE STORE SALES UP 7% GLOBALLY; UP 12% IN U.S. AND DOUBLE DIGITS INTERNATIONALLY, EX- CHINA.STARBUCKS - NET REVENUES FOR NORTH AMERICA SEGMENT GREW 17% OVER Q2 FY21 TO $5.4 BILLION IN Q2 FY22. ((Reuters.Briefs@thomsonreuters.com;)).

4562902.headline: Starbucks Corp - Board Of Directors Has Approved A Dividend Of $0.49 Per Share Of Outstanding Common Stock
4562902.description: June 29 (Reuters) - Starbucks Corp <SBUX.O>::STARBUCKS CORP - BOARD OF DIRECTORS HAS APPROVED A DIVIDEND OF $0.49 PER SHARE OF OUTSTANDING COMMON STOCK.

4596945.headline: Starbucks Enters New Era Of Growth Driven By An Unparalleled Reinvention Plan
4596945.description: Sept 13 (Reuters) - Starbucks Corp <SBUX.O>::STARBUCKS ENTERS NEW ERA OF GROWTH DRIVEN BY AN UNPARALLELED REINVENTION PLAN.STARBUCKS CORP- PLANS TO RESUME ITS SHARE BUYBACK YIELDING AN ANNUAL EPS BENEFIT OF ABOUT 1%, NET OF INCREMENTAL INTEREST, BEGINNING IN FY 2024.STARBUCKS CORP - BETWEEN DIVIDENDS AND SHARE BUYBACKS, COMPANY EXPECTS TO RETURN APPROXIMATELY $20 BILLION TO ITS SHAREHOLDERS IN NEXT THREE YEARS.STARBUCKS CORP- GLOBALLY, STARBUCKS EXPECTS TO APPROACH 45,000 STORES BY END OF 2025.STARBUCKS CORP- IS WELL ON TRACK TO REACH APPROXIMATELY 55,000 STORES BY 2030, AS PROJECTED AT ITS 2020 INVESTOR DAY.STARBUCKS - INTRODUCES 3-YEAR FINANCIAL ROADMAP, DELIVERING ANNUAL 7-9% COMPARABLE STORE SALES GROWTH, 10-12% REVENUE GROWTH, 15-20% NON-GAAP EPS GROWTH.STARBUCKS - GROWING STARBUCKS DELIVERS PROGRAM IN U.S. WITH PARTNERSHIP WITH DOORDASH, WHICH WILL EXPAND TO NATIONAL SCALE ALONGSIDE UBEREATS IN FISCAL 2023.STARBUCKS -  ALREADY BEGUN ROLLING OUT CLOVER VERTICA EQUIPMENT TO STORES AND EXPECTS IT WILL BE FULLY DEPLOYED TO ALL U.S. STORES IN NEXT THREE YEARS.

4601624.headline: Starbucks Announces Increase In Quarterly Cash Dividend
4601624.description: Sept 28 (Reuters) - Starbucks Corp <SBUX.O>::STARBUCKS ANNOUNCES INCREASE IN QUARTERLY CASH DIVIDEND.STARBUCKS CORP - APPROVED AN INCREASE IN COMPANY'S QUARTERLY CASH DIVIDEND FROM $0.49 TO $0.53 PER SHARE.

4618159.headline: Starbucks Corp Q4 China Comp Store Sales Down 16%
4618159.description: Nov 3 (Reuters) - Starbucks Corp <SBUX.O>::Q4 CONSOLIDATED NET REVENUES UP 3.3% TO $8.41 BILLION.Q4 GAAP EPS $0.76.Q4 NON-GAAP EPS OF $0.81.Q4 EARNINGS PER SHARE VIEW $0.72, REVENUE VIEW $8.31 BILLION -- REFINITIV IBES DATA.Q4 CHINA COMP STORE SALES DOWN 16%.Q4 COMP STORE SALES UP 7% GLOBALLY; UP 11% IN U.S. AND DOUBLE DIGITS INTERNATIONALLY, EXCLUDING CHINA.Further company coverage: <SBUX.O>. ((Reuters.Briefs@thomsonreuters.com;)).

4632251.headline: Starbucks Declares Quarterly Cash Dividend
4632251.description: Nov 30 (Reuters) - Starbucks Corp <SBUX.O>::STARBUCKS DECLARES QUARTERLY CASH DIVIDEND.BOARD HAS APPROVED QUARTERLY CASH DIVIDEND OF $0.53 PER SHARE OF OUTSTANDING COMMON STOCK.

4653915.headline: Starbucks Reports Q1 Fiscal 2023 Results
4653915.description: Feb 2 (Reuters) - Starbucks Corp <SBUX.O>::STARBUCKS REPORTS Q1 FISCAL 2023 RESULTS.STARBUCKS CORP - COMPANY REAFFIRMS 2023 FULL YEAR GUIDANCE.STARBUCKS CORP- QTRLY INTERNATIONAL COMPARABLE STORE SALES DECREASED 13%.STARBUCKS CORP- QTRLY CHINA COMPARABLE STORE SALES DECREASED 29%.

4653879.headline: Starbucks - Excluding China, QTRLY Comparative Sales Up In Double Digits Internationally
4653879.description: Feb 2 (Reuters) - Starbucks Corp <SBUX.O>::STARBUCKS QTRLY EARNINGS PER SHARE $0.74; QTRLY ADJUSTED EARNINGS PER SHARE $0.75; QTRLY CONSOL NET REVENUE UP 8% TO $8.7 BILLION.STARBUCKS QTRLY COMPARATIVE SALES ROSE 5% GLOBALLY, 10% IN THE UNITED STATES.Q1 EARNINGS PER SHARE VIEW $0.77, REVENUE VIEW $8.78 BILLION -- REFINITIV IBES DATA.STARBUCKS - EXCLUDING CHINA, QTRLY COMPARATIVE SALES UP IN DOUBLE DIGITS INTERNATIONALLY.
